<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>守护者</title><description>卫报全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> https://theguardian.com <item><title><![CDATA[Famous Sycamore Gap tree at Hadrian’s Wall found cut down]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/sep/28/famous-sycamore-gap-tree-at-hadrians-wall-found-apparently-cut-down]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-28T11:29:20Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ae571e12b3db93b298c601382d5e0ab9c13316b7/0_56_3500_2101 /master/3500.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=506f565579551f03c2c44b00ab0ae08b&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;被砍伐的 Sycamore Gap 树的警戒线&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;警方已展开调查诺森伯兰郡哈德良长城的梧桐树是全国上镜率最高的树木之一，周四上午被发现被砍伐。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这棵世界著名的树，被选为年度最佳树木。林地信托竞赛 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/gallery/2016/sep/19/2016-woodland-trust-tree-of-the-year-shortlist-in-pictures&quot;>; 2016 年&lt;/a>;，并在 1991 年电影《罗宾汉：盗贼王子》中出现，被认为是被故意砍倒的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周四早上拍摄的照片显示，它的底部似乎被锯断了。树干用电锯。这棵梧桐树估计已有数百年历史，此前曾矗立在诺森伯兰郡国家公园风景如画的小山谷中。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-canonical-url=&quot;https://twitter.com/TwiceBrewedCo/status/ 1707325696064766325&quot;>; &lt;blockquote>; &lt;p>;哈德良长城上的早晨绝对令人心碎。不再有梧桐间隙。 &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/MWb49kZlaG&quot;>;pic.twitter.com/MWb49kZlaG&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>;— Twice Brewed Brew Co. (@TwiceBrewedCo) &lt;a href=&quot;https:// twitter.com/TwiceBrewedCo/status/1707325696064766325?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;2023 年 9 月 28 日&lt;/a>; &lt;/blockquote>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;在一份声明中，诺森伯兰国家公园管理局表示“可以确认可悲的是，梧桐峡的那棵著名的树一夜之间就倒下了。我们有理由相信它是被故意砍伐的。我们正在与对这一标志性东北地标感兴趣的相关机构和合作伙伴合作，一旦了解更多细节，我们将发布。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Sycamore Gap 被评选为 2016 年英国年度树Woodland Trust 屡获殊荣，深受世界各地人们的喜爱。诺森伯兰国家公园管理局希望公众此时不要访问该地点，同时我们将与合作伙伴一起查明发生的情况并确保该地点的安全。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;诺森布里亚警方发言人表示： “我们可以确认，在诺森伯兰郡的 Sycamore Gap 树受损后，已经启动了调查。 “正在调查以确定是否存在任何刑事犯罪。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;29a0a336f92568b4ccc1a4576a3555feefbdffa0&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/29a0a336f92568b4ccc1a4576a3555feefbdffa0/ 785_1317_3991_2395/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;2022 年 1 月拍摄的树&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;2022 年 1 月拍摄的树。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Oli斯卡夫/法新社/盖蒂图片社&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;当地人对这一消息感到震惊。当地的一家名为“Humshaugh 的皇冠旅馆”的酒吧发帖称：“今天早上的消息绝对令人震惊，Sycamore Gap 已经不复存在了，一些无脑的白痴似乎连夜把它砍掉了。人们脑子里到底在想什么？&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“每年我们都会迎来成千上万期待一睹这棵名树的人们。非常悲伤的一天。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;作者 LJ Ross 写道：“听说失去这棵标志性的美丽树，我感到非常悲伤，它是我第二本书的灵感来源。我不知道为什么它被砍倒，目前有很多猜测，但我只能希望有一个很好的理由。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 28 Sep 2023 19:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Michael Gambon, star of Harry Potter and The Singing Detective, dies aged 82]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/sep/28/michael-gambon-star-of-harry-potter-and-the-singing-detective-dies-aged-82]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-28T11:39:05Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/44c9bc408424186b53b2f9ab49be65c6188a6552/0_2675_5477_3286 /master/5477.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=f4e15fa773d84ccdaabe8df29b4e0d46&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;2000 年的迈克尔·甘本。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;爵士 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www. theguardian.com/stage/2014/may/20/michael-gambon-interview&quot;>;迈克尔·甘本&lt;/a>;，其非凡的演艺生涯使他从劳伦斯·奥利维尔新生的国家剧院到&lt;a href=&quot;https:/ /www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2012/feb/02/singing-detective-addictive-bbc4&quot;>;歌唱侦探&lt;/a>;和&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu:// list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/film/harrypotter&quot;>;哈利·波特电影&lt;/a>;，已去世，享年 82 岁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;代表妻子 Lady Lady 发表声明公关克莱尔·多布斯 (Clair Dobbs) 发布的甘本和儿子弗格斯 (Fergus) 表示：“我们悲痛地宣布迈克尔·甘本爵士去世。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“亲爱的丈夫和父亲，迈克尔与妻子安妮和儿子在医院安详地去世。肺炎发作后，弗格斯守在他的床边。迈克尔已经 82 岁了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们请求您在这个痛苦的时刻尊重我们的隐私，并感谢您发出的支持和爱的信息。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;被称为“伟大的甘本”，令人难忘拉尔夫·理查德森 (Ralph Richardson) 深受一代又一代演员的钦佩，他在 &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/culture/pinter&quot;>;Pinter&lt;/a >;、&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/culture/beckett&quot;>;贝克特&lt;/a>; 和 &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list /mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/stage/alanayckbourn&quot;>;艾克伯恩&lt;/a>;。 1987 年，艾克伯恩执导了阿瑟·米勒 (Arthur Miller) 的 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/stage/theatreblog/2015/may/04/great-performances-michael-gambon-in-a-view- from-the-bridge-national-theatre-1987&quot;>;《桥上的风景》&lt;/a>;，甘本因其在布鲁克林码头工人埃迪·卡本 (Eddie Carbone) 中的表演而获得奥利维尔奖。甘本还主演了艾克伯恩雄心勃勃的三部曲《诺曼征服》。其他重要角色包括 1980 年在国家剧院上演的布莱希特的《伽利略传》中的同名科学家，以及大卫·黑尔的《天窗》中返回探望前情人的餐馆老板，这为他赢得了 90 年代中期百老汇托尼奖的提名。 p>; &lt;p>;甘本凭借彼得格林纳威的&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/film/movie/35645&quot;>;厨师，小偷、他的妻子和她的情人 (1989)&lt;/a>; 并继续在主要电影中担任角色，例如 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/film/2000/jan/07/culture.reviews1 &quot;>;断头谷&lt;/a>;、内幕人士和&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/film/2002/feb/01/1&quot;>;戈斯福德公园&lt;/a>;。然后，他戴着飘逸的胡须和流苏帽子，描绘了哈利·波特的教授阿不思&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/books/2011/aug/31/harry-potter-magical-character-dumbledore&quot;>;阿不思邓布利多在多部大片中出演，在 2002 年理查德·哈里斯去世后接替了他的角色。他在许多电影中展现了丰富的嗓音，包括在两部《帕丁顿熊》电影中饰演帕斯图佐叔叔，以及在科恩兄弟的《万岁》中担任旁白，凯撒！&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;17084fdc0c554341530b042bc2d17cf6bca125ae&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/17084fdc0c554341530b042bc2d17cf6bca125ae/0_219_1435_861/10 00.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;《哈利》中的迈克尔·甘本波特与凤凰社。” width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;《哈利·波特与凤凰社》中的迈克尔·甘本。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Allstar/Warner Bros/Sportsphoto Ltd&lt;/span>; &lt; /figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;甘本 (Gambon) 身材魁梧，面容忧郁，他形容自己看起来像一家百货公司的经理，是一个“又大又有趣的老混蛋”，而艾克伯恩则称他为“奇妙的、无限的机器，就像兰博基尼”。甘本受到观众的喜爱，其强大的影响力可以为最轻的材料增加重量，甘本保护自己的隐私，不情愿地接受采访。 2004 年，他&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/film/2004/feb/29/theatre&quot;>;告诉《观察家报》&lt;/a>;：“我只是缓慢地前进，试图闭嘴。 ”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;甘本 15 岁就离开了学校，与许多同龄人不同，他没有在戏剧学校接受任何正式训练，而是通过在业余作品中表演来获得经验。 1940 年出生于都柏林；他的父亲搬到伦敦，并在第二次世界大战期间担任预备警察。战争结束后，甘本被母亲带到英国与他团聚。后来他们搬到了肯特郡，16 岁时，他开始在维克斯·阿姆斯特朗工厂担任工程学徒。他开始在业余剧院担任布景师，然后最终在伦敦的 Unity 剧院和塔剧院的舞台上担任小角色。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他通过撒谎虚张声势地进入了他的第一个职业角色。关于他的经历，他在都柏林首次亮相，在《奥赛罗》中扮演一个小角色。 22岁时，他在伦敦西区首次亮相，作为替补演员出演了《The Bed-Sitting Room》。他还在皇家宫廷参加了由乔治·迪瓦恩和威廉·加斯基尔开办的表演课程。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;5a50b2d4bcab65df2ee08b3f5db7567d01c8aadf&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk /5a50b2d4bcab65df2ee08b3f5db7567d01c8aadf/0_0_2400_1600/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;迈克尔·甘本在《亨利四世》第 1 部分中饰演福斯塔夫。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;667&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;迈克尔·甘本 (Michael Gambon) 在《亨利四世》第 1 部分中饰演福斯塔夫。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Tristram Kenton/the Guardian&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt; /figure>; &lt;p>;Gambon 表示，在自己出演莎士比亚作品之前，他从未看过莎士比亚的作品。他在国家剧院扮演过莎士比亚的小角色，并在奥利维尔本人面前扮演了理查德三世（最近由劳伦斯·奥利维尔标志性地扮演），为剧团试镜。他与奥利维尔一起出演了国家剧院的《奥赛罗》，以及彼得·奥图尔主演的《哈姆雷特》。然后，在奥利维尔的建议下，甘本离开国家剧院，加入伯明翰话剧团，以获得更大的角色，其中包括《奥赛罗》的标题部分。 30 岁时，他在比林汉姆的一部作品中扮演麦克白，他称这部作品的背景设定在外太空。 80年代初，他在&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.rsc.org.uk/king-lear/past-products/in-focus-adrian-noble-1982&quot;>;皇家莎士比亚剧团&lt;/ a>; 在阿德里安·诺布尔 (Adrian Noble) 制作的《李尔王》和《安东尼与克利奥帕特拉》中演出，有时两部作品都在同一天演出，后者的演出速度极快。 2005 年，尼古拉斯·海特纳 (Nicholas Hytner) 在国家剧院执导的&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2005/may/05/theatre1&quot;>;亨利四世，第 1 部分和第 2 部分&lt;/a>;中饰演福斯塔夫戏剧。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在电视上，他因讲述两个截然不同的侦探的电视剧而大受欢迎。第一个是丹尼斯·波特的黑色音乐&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2012/feb/02/singing-detective-addictive-bbc4&quot;>;歌唱侦探&lt;/ a>;，这使他成为一名因银屑病关节炎住院的悬疑小说家。第二部是梅格雷惊悚片，饰演比利时作家乔治·西默农笔下的同名巴黎警察。他还在托尼·库什纳的《美国天使》电视版中与西蒙·卡洛一起扮演天使。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;b3b69809740c3a908666ea234fae579d4ae90af6&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co. uk/b3b69809740c3a908666ea234fae579d4ae90af6/0_0_2464_1648/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;2004 年《终局之战》中的李·埃文斯和迈克尔·甘本。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;669&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;2004 年《Endgame》中的李·埃文斯 (Lee Evans) 和迈克尔·甘本 (Michael Gambon)。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Tristram Kenton/the Guardian&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt; /figure>; &lt;p>;出现在塞缪尔·贝克特戏剧&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2004/mar/11/theatre&quot;>;Endgame&lt;/a>;后，&lt;a href=&quot; https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2006/jul/01/theatre&quot;>;呃乔&lt;/a>;，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2010/sep/26 /michael-gambon-krapps-last-tape-duchess&quot;>;克拉普的最后一盘磁带&lt;/a>; 和&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2012/oct/12/samuel-beckett-all -that-fall-michael-billington-review&quot;>;整个秋天&lt;/a>;，甘本开始退出舞台工作。 2014年，他说他很难记住自己的台词：“我对此感到难过。我喜欢剧院，但我无法想象自己再次扮演重要角色。” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2009/oct/02/michael-gambon-alan-bennett&quot;>;2009 年，疾病导致他退出&lt;/a>;主演艾伦·贝内特 (Alan Bennett) 的《The》国家剧院的《艺术习惯》，就在开幕之夜前几周，由理查德·格里菲思取代。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;哈罗德·品特的戏剧为甘本带来了一些他最好的角色，包括《背叛》三角恋中的杰瑞和优雅的赫斯特在无人区。当他停止在舞台上表演后，至少可以在 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/JamieLloydCo/status/1037328546505605121&quot;>;Jamie Lloyd 制作的 Mountain Language&lt;/a>; 中听到他丰富、明确的声音。 2018 年西区 Pinter 季的全明星 Pinter。&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot; _blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 28 Sep 2023 19:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[EU threatens sales bans to block use of western parts in Russian drones]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/28/eu-threatens-sales-bans-to-block-use-of-western-parts-in-russian-drones]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-28T08:30:22Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/30f7e6d1886ab278ddd332ef63aeade709cb9116/0_70_2993_1796 /master/2993.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=6e54ef786453ea4a5a04caf8cde7376b&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;5 月份在基辅展出的 Shahed-136 无人机的部件&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;布鲁塞尔已警告欧洲企业和政府表示，它可以禁止向土耳其和其他国家出售某些零部件，伊朗和俄罗斯从这些国家采购袭击乌克兰城市的无人机和其他武器的零部件。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;欧盟委员会的评论是在&lt; a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/27/revealed-europes-role-in-the-making-of-Russia-killer-drones&quot;>;泄露给 47 的守护者页文件&lt;/a>;，其中乌克兰政府详细介绍了西方技术的使用情况，并呼吁使用远程导弹攻击俄罗斯、伊朗和叙利亚的无人机生产基地。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;乌克兰文件提交给七国集团政府在 8 月份声称，在过去三个月中，使用含有西方技术的无人机对城市进行了 600 次袭击。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt; a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/27/revealed-europes-role-in-the-making-of-Russia-killer-drones&quot;>;揭晓：欧洲在制定过程中的角色俄罗斯杀手无人机&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;包括一家英国跨国公司的波兰子公司在内的五家欧洲公司被指定为已识别组件的原始制造商。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;没有迹象表明其零部件被识别的西方公司有任何不当行为。该报称：“伊朗无人机的生产已经进行了调整，大部分使用现有的商业组件，但其供应控制不佳或根本不受控制。” 据称，海关信息显示“几乎所有进口到伊朗原产于土耳其、印度、哈萨克斯坦、乌兹别克斯坦、越南和哥斯达黎加”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;欧盟委员会发言人表示，有证据表明零部件是通过这些国家采购的，这表明欧盟制裁正在“对其目标造成巨大压力” ”但成员国需要加强执法。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他说：“这意味着要密切关注在欧盟出口商不知情的情况下再出口欧盟受制裁商品的外国经营者。针对这种情况，我们已寻求第三国当局的支持，以确保从欧盟出口到这些国家的货物不会到达俄罗斯。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“欧盟制裁特使戴维·奥沙利文 (David O&#39;Sullivan)与第三国司法管辖区密切合作，确保我们的制裁不被规避。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;发言人表示，这一举措已显示出一些“初步切实成果”，并且已经制定了“受制裁战地物资优先清单” ”，“哪些企业应该进行特别的尽职调查，哪些第三国不得向俄罗斯出口”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他补充道：“然而，在某些情况下，这些外交努力可能被证明是不够的，或者可能会出现问题。”根本就没有任何意愿去制作它们。如果没有其他办法，那么唯一剩下的选择就是使用欧盟的反规避工具，停止向这些第三国出口我们最关心的特定商品。该工具将允许欧盟禁止将这些商品出口到用于规避我们制裁的国家，并禁止提供相关服务。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“第 10 个制裁方案包括第一个制裁方案七个伊朗实体一直在使用欧盟组件并向俄罗斯提供军用“沙赫德”无人机来攻击乌克兰的民用基础设施。这应该对其他公司和国际贸易商产生强有力的威慑，让他们不再容忍规避出口限制的行为。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-interactive=&quot;https://interactive.guim.co.uk/embed/iframe -wrapper/0.1/boot.js&quot; data-canonical-url=&quot;https://interactive.guim.co.uk/uploader/embed/2022/10/drone-zip/giv-6562n93d2p4i016H/&quot; data-alt=&quot; Shahed-136 无人机&quot;>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://interactive.guim.co.uk/uploader/embed/2022/10/drone-zip/giv-6562n93d2p4i016H/&quot;>;交互式&lt;/a>; &lt;/figure >; &lt;p>;俄罗斯在乌克兰使用的 Shahed-131 和 136 无人机中发现的欧洲制造物品包括燃油泵、晶体管、电源管理电路和微处理器。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;英国影子国防部长约翰·希利 (John Healey) ，敦促英国政府在这个问题上与委员会密切合作。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他说：“令人严重关切的是，俄罗斯使用的武器中继续出现西方制造的部件，以实施其残酷和残酷的军事行动。”非法入侵乌克兰。乌克兰揭露此类双重用途技术是正确的，必须优先通过堵塞制裁制度的漏洞来支持他们的斗争。政府应与欧盟委员会等盟友和合作伙伴合作，确保切断零部件的流动。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在乌克兰总统弗拉基米尔·泽连斯基 (Volodymr Zelenskiy) 办公室工作的制裁顾问弗拉迪内·弗拉休克 (Vladyne Vlasiuk) 表示，目前有关无人机部件的情况“令人沮丧”，游说工作自六月以来一直在进行。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他说：“当然，很难向乌克兰人民和乌克兰军人解释清楚。英国政府发言人表示，他们已经实施了“最大规模、最严厉的经济制裁”。他表示：“我们很清楚，任何被发现直接或向俄罗斯销售或出口受制裁商品的英国公司或其子公司间接地，可能违反制裁法，并可能面临重罚或监禁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们正在与合作伙伴密切合作，协调措施并不断审查我们的制裁 - 包括解决潜在规避问题。” &lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 28 Sep 2023 18:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Swiss glaciers lose 10% of their volume in two years]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/sep/28/swiss-glaciers-lose-tenth-volume-in-two-years-climate-crisis]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-28T09:38:54Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c7612f299a4ff74e28951f7bc6e910c8f3cf52d6/0_154_5262_3157 /master/5262.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=d788a7186a8a3c812ede8bd8d9d57645&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;瑞士奥伯戈姆斯罗纳冰川上的瑞士国旗&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;瑞士冰川已经损失了 10%一份报告发现，它们的体积在短短两年内就减少了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;科学家表示，燃烧化石燃料造成的气候破坏是导致夏季异常炎热和冬季雪量极少的原因，这导致加速融化。 2022年和2023年炎热夏季的损失量与1960年至1990年期间的损失量相同。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;瑞士科学院的分析发现，今年瑞士冰川总体积的4%消失了，有记录以来第二大年度跌幅。最大降幅出现在 2022 年，当时下降了 6%，这是自测量开始以来最大的解冻。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https:// www.theguardian.com/environment/ng-interactive/2021/apr/29/visualized-glaciers-now-and-then&quot;>;可视化：冰川的过去和现在&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;专家们已经停止测量一些冰川上的冰，因为基本上已经没有了。瑞士冰川监测机构 (Glamos) 负责监测 176 条冰川，最近停止了对瑞士中部乌里州圣安纳芬冰川的测量，因为该冰川大部分已融化。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Glamos 负责人马蒂亚斯·胡斯 (Matthias Huss) 表示：“我们只剩下一些死冰了。气候变化使得此类极端事件更有可能发生，而极端气象事件也非常糟糕。如果我们继续按照这个速度......我们每年都会看到这样糟糕的年份。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他说，由于 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/ 的速度，小冰川正在消失。环境/2019/apr/09/三分之二-冰川-阿尔卑斯-高山-注定-气候变化-冰&quot;>;冰损失&lt;/a>;。他说，为了阻止瑞士失去冰川，需要停止排放，但他补充说，即使世界设法将气温升高到比工业化前水平高出 1.5 摄氏度，预计瑞士也只会保留三分之一的冰川体积。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;他说，这意味着“所有小冰川无论如何都会消失，而大冰川将会小得多”。但他强调，至少“阿尔卑斯山最高地区会有一些冰和一些冰川，我们可以向我们的子孙展示”。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2021/may/04/melting-ice-reveals-first-world-war-relics-in-italian-alps&quot;>;冰川融化揭示了第一次世界大战意大利阿尔卑斯山的遗迹&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;瑞士阿尔卑斯山今年经历了创纪录的温暖。 8 月，即融化高峰月，瑞士气象局发现，降水结冰的海拔在一夜之间创下新纪录，达到 5,289 米（17,350 英尺），比勃朗峰的海拔还要高。这超过了去年5,184米的记录。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;由于冰雪融化，山上的景色正在发生变化。胡斯有记录以来首次发现冰川舌旁边形成了新的湖泊，以及从变薄的冰层中露出的裸露岩石。随着冰盖缩小，长期消失在冰层下的尸体已被找到。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;瑞士的记录主要可追溯到 1960 年，一些冰川的记录可追溯到 1914 年。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 28 Sep 2023 17:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Nagorno-Karabakh’s separatist government says it will dissolve]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/28/nagorno-karabakh-separatist-government-says-dissolve-azerbaijan-armenia]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-28T09:42:34Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/134bef818349398f52a15915965d7cbb01a7a992/113_372_4337_2603 /master/4337.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=94b6721ac3af133576ce25e5753ace02&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;人们坐在卡车后面&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫分离主义政府宣布它会自行解散，这个未被承认的共和国将在明年初不复存在。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;亚美尼亚自封的纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫共和国总统萨姆维尔·沙赫拉马尼扬签署了一项解散所有国家机构的法令卡拉巴赫亚美尼亚当局在一份声明中表示，到 2024 年 1 月 1 日。该法令称，从那天起，共和国将不复存在。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;超过一半的纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫人口已逃往亚美尼亚，该国在&lt;a href=&quot;之后将其描述为“种族清洗” https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/19/azerbaijan-launches-anti-terrorist-campaign-in-disputed-nagorno-karabakh-region&quot;>;上周24小时闪电战&lt;/a>;该法令还表示，当地居民必须“熟悉阿塞拜疆共和国提出的重返社会条件”，并做出“独立和个人的决定”是否留下或离开该地区。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿塞拜疆军队的袭击迫使地方当局同意放下武器并开始就纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫“重新融入”阿塞拜疆问题进行谈判。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫于 1991 年宣布独立，由亚美尼亚族分离主义当局统治了大约 30 年。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;亚美尼亚总理发言人 Nikol Pashinyan 周四表示，有 68,386 名纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫人已越境进入该国——据信在最新一轮战斗之前，12万亚美尼亚族人中一半以上居住在卡拉巴赫。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-interactive=&quot;https://interactive.guim.co.uk/嵌入/iframe-wrapper/0.1/boot.js&quot; data-canonical-url=&quot;https://interactive.guim.co.uk/uploader/embed/2023/09/nagorno_karabackh_detail/giv-13425WK221xEKGVqk/&quot; data-alt= “纳戈尔诺卡拉巴赫地图”>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://interactive.guim.co.uk/uploader/embed/2023/09/nagorno_karabackh_detail/giv-13425WK221xEKGVqk/&quot;>;交互式&lt;/a>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p >;帕希尼扬警告称，未来几天亚美尼亚人不会留在该地区，称这次撤离是“种族清洗”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这是种族清洗的直接行为，我们长期以来一直警告国际社会”帕希尼扬在政府会议上说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他还呼吁“国际行动”对阿塞拜疆采取“具体行动”。他说：“如果这些声明之后没有相关的政治和法律决定，那么谴责就变成了对正在发生的事情表示同意的行为。”美国国务卿安东尼·布林肯此前曾敦促阿塞拜疆总统伊尔哈姆·阿利耶夫，以避免该地区发生进一步的敌对行动，为其居民提供保证并允许国际观察团进入。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我认为我们将看到卡拉巴赫的绝大多数人前往亚美尼亚”，卡内基欧洲智库高级研究员托马斯·德瓦尔说。 “他们被告知要融入阿塞拜疆这个他们从未参与过的国家，他们中的大多数人甚至不会说阿塞拜疆语言，并被告知要解散当地机构。这是卡拉巴赫大多数人不会接受的提议。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿塞拜疆当局周四宣布，他们已指控该分离主义地区前领导人鲁本·瓦尔达尼扬 (Ruben Vardanyan) 资助恐怖主义和其他罪行。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;瓦尔达尼扬 (Vardanyan) ，一位富商，曾担任纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫共和国国务部长，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/27/former-state-minister-of-nagorno- karabakh-ruben-vardanyan-arrested-by-azerbaijan&quot;>;一天前被拘留&lt;/a>;，当时他试图越境进入亚美尼亚。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;巴库法院裁定应逮捕并安置 Vardanyan审前拘留四个月。&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https:// feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 28 Sep 2023 17:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Plants or bookcases as backdrop on video call really do impress, study finds]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/sep/28/plants-or-bookcases-as-backdrop-on-video-call-really-do-impress-study-finds]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-28T09:00:07Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/42b1841ed4488c8e901b1d52fded14d97dc017b3/0_413_5181_3109 /master/5181.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=412b53b08a05933967dd5a13119294da&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;后台有书架的人在群组视频通话中聊天。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;精心设计视频通话的背景，让自己看起来博览群书，这可能会证明他们的麻烦是正确的，因为研究发现，书架或植物在在线会议中给人留下了最好的印象。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;相比之下，任何想要增添趣味的人具有新奇背景的事情应该三思，因为杜伦大学心理学系的研究人员发现，这会让人们不太可能认为他们正在观看的人是值得信赖或有能力的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https:/ /journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0291444&quot;>;该研究&lt;/a>;使用了 160 多人来评估不同虚拟背景和各种场景下的精选人物图像。面部表情。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;客厅或新奇的背景（在本例中是冰山前的海象）被发现会降低人们对信任和能力的看法。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该研究评估了超过 160 个人的观点，他们被要求评估一系列在各种虚拟背景下以及中性和快乐面部表情的人物图像。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;性别也发挥了作用，因为女性无论背景如何，他们更有可能在信任和能力方面获得高分。拥有快乐的面部表情还可以提高人们对信任和能力的感知水平。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这些图像是通过收集 18 名白人男性和 18 名白人女性的 72 张照片制作的，这些照片要么微笑，要么表情中性。然后，这些面孔被叠加到六个不同的背景上：一间客厅、一间模糊的客厅、一个书柜、橱柜上的室内植物、一面空白的墙壁和冰山前的海象。然后，它们被设计成 Zoom 通话期间的屏幕截图。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;达勒姆大学副教授帕迪·罗斯 (Paddy Ross) 表示：“在新冠疫情在网上改变了很多第一印象的世界里，印象中，你不再只需要考虑你的外表，你还必须考虑你的背景看起来如何。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们想知道的是：如果，我看起来更值得信赖或更有能力，因为，例如，我在一些植物、书柜、客厅前，或者我的客厅很乱，我想模糊它，或者只是一面空白的墙或新奇的背景？”&lt;/p>; &lt;罗斯谈到他们的发现时说道：“背景真的会让你看起来比使用不同背景的人更不值得信任吗？如果您可以坐在书柜或一些室内植物前，我们发现这些是对人的信任和能力进行评级的最佳方式。尽量避免有新奇的背景或你身后的生活空间。我们发现这些是信任和信心评级最差的。模糊的背景是可以的，但如果你能展示植物或书柜，那就是信任和能力的第一印象的最佳选择。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 28 Sep 2023 17:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Ministers meet in Brussels to discuss migration – Europe live]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2023/sep/28/ministers-meet-in-brussels-to-discuss-migration-europe-live]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-28T08:44:48Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/a82df0656f13c2d81592bab7739cd1f98356b3a8/0_109_5088_3053 /master/5088.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=d54315b89ed6baa1260f18108bd62603&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;意大利西西里兰佩杜萨岛，一艘载着海上获救人员的意大利海岸警卫队船只在游船之间经过。 &lt;/div>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https:/ /feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br >;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 28 Sep 2023 16:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Vietnam jails leading climate activist Hoang Thi Minh Hong for tax evasion]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/28/vietnam-jails-leading-climate-activist-hoang-thi-minh-hong-for-tax-evasion]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-28T05:50:06Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7e0daa553cf36d3ecc36c51a1478312b7a3edcae/192_560_4550_2730 /master/4550.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=41f12d56f67536a074f9ef3e6edea0f5&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;cyclist street hanoi vietnam&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;A leading Vietnamese climate activist has been jailed for tax evasion, the latest environmentalist put behind bars by the country&#39;s communist government.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A court in Ho Chi Minh City sentenced Hoang Thi Minh Hong to three years in prison for dodging $275,000 in taxes related to her environmental campaign group Change, her lawyer , Nguyen Van Tu, said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The 50-year-old is at least the fifth environmental campaigner to be jailed on tax evasion charges in the last two years as Vietnam&#39;s authoritarian government steps up a crackdown on activists. &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Her husband, Hoang Vinh Nam, said he was “disappointed” at the verdict.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https: //www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jun/02/vietnam-outcry-after-leading-climate-activist-arrested-accused-of-tax-evasion&quot;>;Vietnam: outcry after leading climate activist arrested, accused of tax evasion&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;“The sentence given to Hong today was too heavy,” he said. “I think it was unfair to Hong. The defence lawyer did his best but his arguments were not considered properly.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;State media said the charges related to revenue generated by Change from 2012 to 2022. Hong admitted the charges and along with her family paid the state 3.5bn dong ($145,000) in return for leniency, state media said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Hong founded Change to mobilise Vietnamese, particularly young people, to take action on environmental issues including climate change, the illegal wildlife trade and pollution. But she abruptly shut down the group last year after four environmental and human rights activists were jailed for tax evasion.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“This conviction is a total fraud, nobody should be fooled by it,” said Ben Swanton, the co-director of The 88 Project, which advocates for human rights in Vietnam. “This is yet another example of the law being weaponised to persecute climate activists who are fighting to save the planet.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Earlier this month Hanoi police detained the director of the Vietnam Initiative for Energy Transition, an independent energy policy thinktank.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Ngo Thi To Nhien, who has worked with the EU, World Bank and UN, was reportedly working on the implementation plan for Vietnam&#39;s Just Energy Transition Partnership, a $15bn G7-funded project to help wean Vietnam off fossil fuels.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;No official information on Nhien&#39;s accusation has been made public.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Hong has been recognised internationally for her work: she joined the Obama Foundation Scholars program in New York in 2018 and was listed by Forbes among the 50 most influential Vietnamese women in 2019.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;When she was detained in May, the UN&#39;s human rights body was among many international groups to voice concern, warning of the “chilling effect” of tax cases against civil society groups.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Among the four green activists jailed last year was &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2022/feb/09/award-winning-vietnamese-environmentalist-arrested-as-rights-groups-fear-clamp-down&quot;>;Nguy Thi Khanh&lt;/a>;, a globally recognised climate and energy campaigner who won the Goldman Environmental Prize in 2018. She spent nearly a year in jail before she was released last month.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Agence France-Presse and Reuters contributed to this report&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 28 Sep 2023 13:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Japan’s top companies cut ties with Johnny Kitagawa’s J-pop agency over sexual abuse scandal]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/28/japans-top-companies-cut-ties-with-johnny-kitagawas-j-pop-agency-over-sexual-abuse-scandal]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-28T04:59:48Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4f4255cbe8de6818f32cb0bf4e11d661af946393/663_123_2429_1457/master/2429.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=5f1026c16a3a94f5014eb003e8bac523&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Johnny Kitagawa on a tv screen&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Some of &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/world/japan&quot;>;Japan&lt;/a>;&#39;s best-known companies have cut ties with a powerful talent agency whose founder was accused of sexually assaulting hundreds of teenage boys, in a scandal that has rocked the country&#39;s entertainment industry.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The public broadcaster NHK said this week it would not sign new contracts with stars from Johnny &amp;amp; Associates until it was convinced the firm had properly addressed the scandal.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We will suspend making new offers until we make sure that it is taking concrete steps to compensate the victims and take prevention measures,” NHK&#39;s president, Nobuo Inaba, told reporters.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The commercial backlash has gathered pace since the agency&#39;s then president, Julie Fujishima, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/07/head-of-johnny-kitagawa-j-pop-agency-resigns-over-sexual-abuse-scandal&quot;>;admitted for the first time this month&lt;/a>; that its late founder, Johnny Kitagawa, had abused young men and boy who were hoping to make it in Japan&#39;s cutthroat pop scene.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Fujishima, who is Kitagawa&#39;s niece, announced her resignation as president of Johnny &amp;amp; Associates, although she continues to hold 100% of its shares.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/mar/07/predator-the-secret-scandal-of-j-pop-review-japan-johnny-kitagawa&quot;>;Predator: The Secret Scandal of J-Pop review – a breathtaking look at Japan&#39;s paedophile boyband &#39;god&#39;&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;The agency&#39;s decision to retain its name sparked criticism from victims and firms that use its performers in advertising campaigns. The agency&#39;s board met last week to discuss a potential name change, with an announcement due on Monday.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;NHK&#39;s decision means the agency&#39;s top stars are unlikely to appear in its popular New Year&#39;s Eve singing contest &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2012/nov/29/japanese-tv-singing-omits-south-korean&quot;>;Kohaku Uta Gassen&lt;/a>; (the Red and White Song Battle), a TV fixture since the early 1950s.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;McDonald&#39;s Japan, Japan Airlines, Nissan and the drinks manufacturers Kirin and Suntory are among the firms that have ended or suspended their commercial association with the agency, after a panel of experts &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/30/niece-of-j-pop-mogul-johnny-kitagawa-should-resign-over-abuse-allegations-panel-says&quot;>;concluded in August&lt;/a>; that the agency had covered up Kitagawa&#39;s sexual abuse for decades.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Using the agency&#39;s talent would mean we are tolerating child abuse,” Takeshi Niinami, the president of Suntory, told reporters, according to the Kyodo news agency.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Kitagawa, who died in 2019 aged 87, was behind a string of successful J-pop groups, including &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/jan/19/japan-rejoices-as-boyband-smap-says-it-is-not-splitting-up&quot;>;Smap&lt;/a>; and Arashi, who built huge followings in Japan and across Asia.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Allegations that Kitagawa, who founded the agency in 1962, had abused young men hired by his agency first appeared in the weekly magazine Shūkan Bunshun in 1999.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Kitagawa sued Bunshun for libel and was awarded damages, but the judgment was partially overturned on appeal, with the Tokyo high court ruling in 2004 that the magazine had sufficient reason to publish the allegations against him. Kitagawa&#39;s appeal was rejected by the supreme court. He was never charged with a crime.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The allegations against Kitagawa, ignored for decades by Japanese newspapers and TV networks, have sparked a reckoning with the country&#39;s record on addressing sexual abuse.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The expert panel said it believed Japanese media had decided not to report the allegations, fearing they would lose access to popular artists represented by Johnny&#39;s, as the firm is widely known.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;This month, the government said it would open a temporary hotline, staffed by qualified counsellors, for male victims of sexual abuse. “We hope victims will feel safe and can use the service without hesitation,” Ayuko Kato, a minister in charge of child-related policies, told reporters.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The agency said it had set up a panel of former judges who will determine how much compensation will be paid to survivors of Kitagawa&#39;s alleged abuse.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Kitagawa&#39;s conduct became the focus of media attention after the broadcast in March of a BBC documentary, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/mar/07/predator-the-secret-scandal-of-j-pop-review-japan-johnny-kitagawa&quot;>;Predator: The Secret Scandal of J-Pop&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Soon after, Kauan Okamoto, who had been hired by the agency as a 15-year-old, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/apr/12/ohnny-kitagawa-former-j-pop-idol-kauan-okamoto-alleges-sexual-abuse-japan-music-mogul&quot;>;went public&lt;/a>; with allegations of abuse, telling reporters he had been sexually assaulted on at least 15 occasions at Kitagawa&#39;s luxury apartment in Tokyo. Several other former members of the agency came forward with similar allegations.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;&lt;span>;•&lt;/span>; In the UK, the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nspcc.org.uk/&quot;>;NSPCC&lt;/a>; offers support to children on 0800 1111, and adults concerned about a child on 0808 800 5000. The National Association for People Abused in Childhood (&lt;a href=&quot;https://napac.org.uk/&quot;>;Napac&lt;/a>;) offers support for adult survivors on 0808 801 0331. In the US, call or text the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.childhelp.org/hotline/&quot;>;Childhelp&lt;/a>; abuse hotline on 800-422-4453. In Australia, children, young adults, parents and teachers can contact the &lt;a href=&quot;https://kidshelpline.com.au/&quot;>;Kids &lt;/a>;&lt;/em>;&lt;em>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://kidshelpline.com.au/&quot;>;Helpline&lt;/a>;&lt;/em>;&lt;em>; on 1800 55 1800, or &lt;a href=&quot;https://bravehearts.org.au/&quot;>;Bravehearts&lt;/a>; on 1800 272 831, and adult survivors can contact &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.blueknot.org.au/&quot;>;Blue Knot Foundation&lt;/a>; on 1300 657 380. Other sources of help can be found at &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.childhelplineinternational.org/child-helplines/child-helpline-network/&quot;>;Child &lt;/a>;&lt;/em>;&lt;em>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.childhelplineinternational.org/child-helplines/child-helpline-network/&quot;>;Helpline&lt;/a>;&lt;/em>;&lt;em>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.childhelplineinternational.org/child-helplines/child-helpline-network/&quot;>;s International&lt;/a>;&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 28 Sep 2023 13:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Kosovo accuses Serbia of involvement in paramilitary ambush]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/28/kosovo-accuses-serbia-of-involvement-in-paramilitary-ambush]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-28T05:00:18Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/3e5f2ae36bbbb3925a94a5eddb9818f3ed235293/0_31_5282_3171/master/5282.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=88657ec99973de5bf21faebf0b93bc82&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Armed police in bulletproof vests stand around a police truck under Kosovan flags&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Kosovo has accused Serbia of being behind a paramilitary group which ambushed a police patrol and clashed with Kosovan forces on Sunday.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The authorities in Priština displayed an array of modern weaponry they said the group was using, including two Serbian-made armoured cars and a grenade launcher, alongside a document allegedly showing the grenade launcher, made by the Zastava arms company, had been supplied by the Serbian army.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/25/arms-cache-found-after-ethnic-serb-gunmen-storm-village-in-kosovo&quot;>;Arms cache found after ethnic Serb gunmen storm village in Kosovo&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;The Kosovan government also claimed that the group&#39;s leader was a prominent Kosovo Serb politician loyal to the Serbian president, Aleksandar Vučić, and that one of three paramilitary fighters killed on Sunday was a former bodyguard of Aleksandar Vulin, the Serbian intelligence chief &lt;a href=&quot;https://home.treasury.gov/news/press-releases/jy1606&quot;>;sanctioned by the US in July&lt;/a>; for corruption.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“This group came from Serbia, they are trained in Serbia, financed by them and also equipped by the army of Serbia and its police,” Xhelal Sveçla, the Kosovan interior minister, told the Guardian.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Some of the weapons were taken from the warehouses of the army and handed over to terrorists who came into Kosovo from Serbia.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Sveçla said his ministry had shared the evidence with western embassies and agencies.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“What they wanted to do is to capture territory of Kosovo, and to open a new channel of communication, a new road from Serbia to Kosovo,” he said, adding that the ultimate aim was the partition of the country.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Serbian government has denied involvement with the armed group, but held an official day of mourning for the three dead.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Vučić has sought to justify their actions by falsely claiming, in a meeting with the Russian ambassador to Belgrade, that the Kosovan government was carrying out ethnic cleansing.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Kosovo alleges that the group was led by Milan Radoičić, the deputy leader of the Belgrade-backed Serb List party, which dominates politics in the four Serb-majority municipalities in northern Kosovo.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Sveçla said his country&#39;s intelligence service believed Radoičić, who has been sanctioned by the US and UK, had been wounded and was recovering in the main military hospital in Belgrade.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The claim could not be independently verified. Radoičić has not made a public statement but Serbia&#39;s foreign minister, Ivica Dačić, claimed a video purporting to show Radoičić among the paramilitaries was a “fraud”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The clash happened at a time when &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/24/kosovan-pm-albin-kurti-says-talks-with-serbia-have-reached-dead-end&quot;>;EU-brokered talks aimed at normalising relations between the two countries are stalled&lt;/a>;, with Vučić vowing he will never recognise Kosovo, and the Kosovan government consequently refusing to establish a semi-autonomous association of Serb municipalities.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The US has been backing the talks and has until now sided with Europe for putting most of the blame for their failure on the Kosovan prime minister, Albin Kurti. But the Biden administration is investigating Belgrade&#39;s involvement in the paramilitary unit, and trying to discover its mission.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;If Vučić is found to have been involved, it could change the approach taken by the US and the EU to negotiations, which have been &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/us-and-eu-leaders-urged-to-change-tack-on-kosovo-serbia-tensions&quot;>;criticised by legislators on both sides of the Atlantic as being biased towards Belgrade&lt;/a>;. It could also lead to sanctions on Serbia.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“It is increasingly clear that there was a scenario at work to provoke a conflict so that the Serbian army would then enter to protect the Serbian people in the north and thus implement the division of Kosovo,” said Sonja Biserko, the president of the &lt;a href=&quot;https://helsinki.org.rs/&quot;>;Helsinki Committee for Human Rights in Serbia&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“This operation, regardless of who is directly responsible for it in Belgrade, has crossed a red line that the west cannot tolerate,” Biserko said. “This situation was not provoked by Kurti, as most in Belgrade comment. On the contrary, he showed maturity and the Kosovo police showed professionalism.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In a briefing paper for the EU, the Kosovan government said “a group of dozens of masked gunmen opened fire on a routine patrol by police officers” on 24 September in the village of Banjska, also known as Banjskë, near the Serbian border.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;One Kosovan police officer was killed, as well as three members of the paramilitary group, and several others were injured in the clashes. The Serb group then withdrew in armoured cars to a monastery near the village, leading to a standoff.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Before Kosovan police were able to take control of the monastery, Sveçla said, some of the paramilitary group were able to slip away and cross into Serbia.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The US secretary of state, Antony Blinken, condemned the attack on the Kosovan police and said: “The perpetrators of this crime must be held accountable via a transparent investigative process.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We call on the governments of Kosovo and Serbia to refrain from any actions or rhetoric which could further inflame tensions.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Blinken urged a “return to the EU-facilitated dialogue”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Edward P Joseph, a former deputy head of mission in Kosovo of the Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe, said that if Belgrade was behind the paramilitary group, the US would have to rethink its approach to the region.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“The point is that the calls for dialogue are empty now that the entire US strategy – to cultivate Vučić&#39;s Serbia as a &#39;partner&#39; – has blown up,” said Joseph, now a senior fellow at the Johns Hopkins University school of advanced international studies in Washington.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Vučić&#39;s denials of knowledge are about as credible as the illusionary US policy towards Serbia.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Shpend Ahmeti, an independent Kosovan politician and former mayor of Priština, said: “It is clear that the next days and weeks will be tense. This is not over.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“The dead militia were treated as heroes and it means that this is a call for more &#39;heroes&#39; but it is also certain that now their capabilities have been decapitated.”&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 28 Sep 2023 13:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Smoking in pregnancy increases risk of premature birth threefold, study finds]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/sep/28/smoking-pregnancy-twice-as-bad-babies-than-previously-thought-study]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-28T04:00:19Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/d901ca6c586349083a2bc87968d2bf82d7f3a91b/0_189_2835_1701/master/2835.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=ff628e5af4ee95d09e68c8c604ff6826&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;a newborn baby boy is checked by nurses in a hospital maternity theatre&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Drinking some tea and coffee does not harm babies, but smoking is twice as bad as previously thought, according to &lt;a href=&quot;https://doi.org/10.1093/ije/dyad123&quot;>;new research&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The NHS recommends that pregnant women should drink &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nhs.uk/pregnancy/keeping-well/foods-to-avoid/#:~:text=Caffeine,low%20birthweight%2C%20and%20even%20miscarriage.&quot;>;no more than 200mg of caffeine a day&lt;/a>;, equivalent to two cups of instant coffee or tea. They should also stop smoking. This is because drinking large amounts of caffeine and smoking have been associated with increased risk of pregnancy complications, premature birth and foetal growth restriction.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;But a study by Cambridge academics has found no evidence that above average caffeine intake throughout pregnancy is linked to pre-term birth or smaller babies. In contrast, the study calculated that women who smoked during pregnancy were nearly three times more likely to give birth prematurely compared with non-smokers – more than double the previous estimate. It also found that babies born to mothers who smoked were four times more likely to be small for their gestational age, putting them at risk of serious complications including breathing difficulties and infections.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The findings come as a separate study by the University of Essex found that a pregnant woman or partner losing their job was associated with &lt;a href=&quot;https://academic.oup.com/humrep/article-lookup/doi/10.1093/humrep/dead183&quot;>;an increased risk of miscarriage or stillbirth&lt;/a>;. The study found a doubling in the chances of a pregnancy miscarrying or resulting in a stillbirth after the loss of a job.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Previous studies looking at the links between smoking, caffeine and adverse pregnancy outcomes have tended to rely on self-reported data to estimate exposure, often at a single time point in pregnancy, which is not always reliable.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;This research, published in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://academic.oup.com/ije&quot;>;International Journal of Epidemiology&lt;/a>;, examined metabolites from smoking (cotinine) and caffeine (paraxanthine) in the blood samples of more than 900 women who took part in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.obgyn.cam.ac.uk/research/pops-2/&quot;>;Pregnancy Outcome Prediction study&lt;/a>; between 2008 and 2012. Researchers analysed levels of cotinine and paraxanthine found in the blood at 12, 20, 28 and 36 weeks of pregnancy and classified the women&#39;s exposure to smoking and caffeine consumption accordingly.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/sep/14/stillbirths-in-uk-rose-in-2021-for-first-time-in-seven-years&quot;>;Stillbirths in UK rose in 2021 for first time in seven years&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Prof Gordon Smith, the head of the department of obstetrics and gynaecology at the University of Cambridge, said the findings underlined the importance of smoking cessation services. “We&#39;ve known for a long time that smoking during pregnancy is not good for the baby, but our study shows that it&#39;s potentially much worse than previously thought,” he said. “It puts the baby at risk of potentially serious complications from growing too slowly in the womb or from being born too soon.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;But Smith said the findings did not mean that pregnant women should start drinking lots of espressos. Studies have shown that very high intake of caffeine, in particular coffee, is linked to a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2020/aug/24/no-safe-level-coffee-drinking-pregnant-women-study-says#:~:text=Four out of five observational,birth weight reported a link.&quot;>;higher risk of miscarriage and still birth&lt;/a>;, which were not included in this research, he pointed out. “We only studied women who consistently had above average levels of caffeine metabolites. We did not study women who had extremely high caffeine intake. Hence, we would not interpret our findings as indicating that current recommendations around caffeine intake should be changed.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Responding to the findings, Fleur Parker, a senior practice coordinator at NCT, said that stopping smoking during pregnancy was beneficial to the health of mother and baby, but that quitting was difficult.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“For many women, increased anxiety about pregnancy, birth and life with a new baby can make it even harder to change the habits they often rely on to manage their anxiety,” she said and advised pregnant women to talk to their midwife for help.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 28 Sep 2023 12:52:01 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>